        "text": "Structures are conditions that limit the domain of connectivity of system operations: they are the conditions for the →[[autopoiesis]] of every system. The con- cept of structure describes the selection of the relations between elements that are accepted in the system. In →meaning-constituting systems, structures cannot merely consist of the relations between elements, since elements are events without duration [→Event]: with their disappearance, the relations also would disappear, and with them the system itself. The selections that become structurally relevant are those that limit the possibilities of recombining the elements (communications or thoughts)."
